f_n(x) = \displaystyle\frac{nx^n}{1+x}
\lim_{n \to \infty}\int^1_0 f_n(x) dx
nx^n
1/(1+x)
(n/(n+1))x^{n+1}/(1+x)^2
1/(1+x)^2
\lim_{n \to \infty}(n/(n+1))x^{n+1}/(1+x)^2=g(x)
g(x)=0
x<1
g(1)=1/4
\int^1_0 nx^n/(1+x)= n/2(n+1)+\int_0^1 (n/(n+1))x^{n+1}/(1+x)^2dx
\lim_{n \to \infty}\int_0^1 (n/(n+1))x^{n+1}/(1+x)^2dx
\lim_{n \to \infty}\int_0^1 (n/(n+1))x^{n+1}/(1+x)^2dx=\int_0^1g(x)dx=0
\lim_{n \to \infty}\int^1_0 nx^n/(1+x)=\lim_{n \to \infty}n/2(n+1)=1/2
